  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" M/s JM Laboratories and Others versus State of Andhra Pradesh and Another pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_1_1256_1264','2025INSC127'); ><font size='4'> <strong>M/S JM LABORATORIES AND OTHERS<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF ANDHRA PRADESH AND ANOTHER </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 1 S.C.R. 1256</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 127</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002582025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : BHUSHAN RAMKRISHNA GAVAI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AUGUSTINE GEORGE MASIH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Non-speaking summoning order issued by Magistrate against the appellants. Petition under Section 482, CrPC filed by the appellants for quashing, dismissed by High Court. Issue as regards the legality of the summoning order and the Non-speaking &ndash; Quashing of: Held: Summoning of an accused in a criminal case is a serious matter &ndash; The order of the Magistrate summoning the accused must reflect that he has applied his mind to the facts of the case and the law applicable thereto &ndash; However, in the present<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 30-01-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 487/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_1_1256_1264','2025INSC127','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</